717627f-b.text:
Broadway, north from West 72nd Street, as photographed across the triangular park that is formed by it's intersection with Amsterdam Avenue. Shown prominently is the ornate Ansonia, an apartment hotel that occupies the entire west frontage from 73rd to 74th Street's. This is detailed in View No. 2. The Central Savings Bank extends from 73rd to 74th Street's between the aforementioned thoroughfares.
July 1930
March 1934
George L. Balgue
Neg.# 1140 (VIEW 2)
